other_tests.procedure_name: CT abdomen and pelvis with contrast
other_tests.findings: The appendix is abnormal in appearance, with a dilated fluid-filled lumen measuring 9-10 mm in diameter. There is moderate appendiceal wall enhancement, and surrounding periappendiceal fat stranding and numerous small lymph nodes. There is no free air or other definite sign of perforation. There is no free fluid in the right lower quadrant, but there is a small amount of free fluid in the lower pelvis around the rectum.
